<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>616093</id>
	<title>When the MacBook Air looses it's connection, Firefox becomes unusable</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Since I got a MacBook Air, I noticed something strange:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">STR:</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">1 Start Firefox, with a working internet connection</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">2 Disconnect the internet connection</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">3 Re-Connect the internet connection</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.5">4 Firefox shows the 'you're offline' screen.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.6">5 Firefox can't be closed normally anymore, it doesn't react to that, a forced shutdown is necessary.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Toggling 'Offline mode' in the menu doesn't help, and this happens especially after I send the Macbook Air to sleep and wake it up again.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">It could be that the Air does something special to the networking, since it's up again immediately after sleep, and Jobs even referred to that during his introduction of the Airs.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
